Nice to see that safety feature actually working in the field.

We do not support VMs at this time. Many of them have buggy decoders that  cause them to make mistakes about 
instruction lengths. This generally results in exploitable holes in the inner sandbox.

Of course a really good VM might actually fool the code that's checking if CPUID is implemented correctly; if so it 
would hopefully not have decoder problems either.

Brad
